cs.ET, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.VLSI, cs.LG

The paper discusses the impact of standard cell layout decomposition on placement for self-aligned double patterning (SADP) technology, which is related to electronic design automation (EDA) and very large scale integration (VLSI) design. Therefore, cs.ET (Electronic Design Automation) and cs.VLSI (Very Large Scale Integration) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses conflict-free layout decomposition, which is related to graph theory and algorithms, making cs.DC (Discrete Mathematics) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions pre-coloring results for standard cells, which is related to graph coloring and optimization, making cs.AR (Computer Science and Game Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a SADP friendly standard cell configuration, which is related to layout generation and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
